examples.en: Roy breathed on his hands and rubbed them together vigorously.
He was genuinely joyed with my gift and shook my hand rather vigorously.
She gave a vigorous defense of her beliefs.
He held a hankie up to his nose and blew vigorously.
How vigorously will the local companies defend their turf?
The plan's success depends on how vigorously the UN will back it up with action.
She remained vigorous into her nineties.
His speech was met with vigorous applause.
